text:
Say I have a logo that links to my root domain homepage. I also have a blog at a subdomain. Templates for the website and blog share the same header partial.

I’ve been using content staging for all the website pages inc. homepage. Is there a way to handle linking to the staged homepage from a live HS blog?

I have the following at the moment, but obviously this tries to link to old content rather than my new, staged homepage. I can hardcode the staged homepage url instead but it’s one more thing to update at site launch, or consider when using content staging for further changes.
```
&lt;a href="{{ company_domain if group else '/' }}"&gt;
  &lt;img&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;
```
